{"version":"https://jsonfeed.org/version/1","title":"personal ✧ errbufferoverfl","description":"Recent content in personal on errbufferoverfl","home_page_url":"https://garden.errbufferoverfl.me/","feed_url":"https://garden.errbufferoverfl.me/tags/personal/index.json","items":[{"title":"the antilibrary","date_published":"2023-05-28T00:00:00+10:00","date_modified":"2023-05-28T00:00:00+10:00","id":"https://garden.errbufferoverfl.me/the-antilibrary/","url":"https://garden.errbufferoverfl.me/the-antilibrary/","content_html":"\u003cblockquote\u003e\n\u003cp\u003ea scholar conscious of the power of [their] antilibrary is not concerned with treating knowledge as a property to possess or consume; rather [\u0026hellip;] how much you don’t know—and how to find out that information when you need it.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e- Giovanni da Col, HAU: Journal of Ethnographic Theory\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/blockquote\u003e\n\u003ch2 id=\"up-next\"\u003eUp Next\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\u003ch2 id=\"current\"\u003eCurrent\u003c/h2\u003e\n\u003cul class=\"section-ul\"\u003e\u003cli class=\"section-li\"\u003e\n        \u003cdiv class=\"section\"\u003e\n            \u003cdiv class=\"meta\"\u003e\n                \n                \u003ca href=\"/books/anarchic-agreements-a-field-guide-to-collective-organising/\"\u003e\u003cimg src=\"/imgs/anarchic-agreements-a-field-guide-to-collective-organising.png\" width=\"96px\"\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\n            \u003c/div\u003e\n            \u003cdiv class=\"desc\" style=\"padding-left: 2em;\"\u003e\n                \u003ch3\u003e\u003ca href=\"/books/anarchic-agreements-a-field-guide-to-collective-organising/\" class=\"internal-link\" data-src=\"/books/anarchic-agreements-a-field-guide-to-collective-organising/\"\u003eAnarchic Agreements, a Field Guide to Collective Organising\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/h3\u003e\n                \u003cp style=\"padding-bottom: 1em; padding-top: 1em;\"\u003eA new world is possible and not just in our hearts. Anarchic Agreements is a quintessential field guide for the revolution, answering the practical questions often left out of works of political theory and philosophy.\u003c/p\u003e\n            \u003c/div\u003e\n        \u003c/div\u003e\n        \u003cul class=\"tags\"\u003e\n            \n            \u003cli\u003e\u003ca href=\"/tags/political-science/\"\u003ePolitical-Science\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n            \n            \u003cli\u003e\u003ca href=\"/tags/anarchy/\"\u003eAnarchy\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n            \n            \u003cli\u003e\u003ca href=\"/tags/anarchism/\"\u003eAnarchism\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n            \n            \u003cli\u003e\u003ca href=\"/tags/constitutions/\"\u003eConstitutions\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n            \n            \u003cli\u003e\u003ca href=\"/tags/history-and-theory/\"\u003eHistory-and-Theory\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n            \n            \u003cli\u003e\u003ca href=\"/tags/book/\"\u003eBook\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n            \n        \u003c/ul\u003e\n    \u003c/li\u003e\u003c/ul\u003e\n\u003ch2 id=\"past\"\u003ePast\u003c/h2\u003e\n\u003cul class=\"section-ul\"\u003e\u003cli class=\"section-li\"\u003e\n        \u003cdiv class=\"section\"\u003e\n            \u003cdiv class=\"meta\"\u003e\n                \n                \u003ca href=\"/books/the-feminist-and-the-sex-offender/\"\u003e\u003cimg src=\"/imgs/the-feminist-and-the-sex-offender.png\" width=\"96px\"\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\n            \u003c/div\u003e\n            \u003cdiv class=\"desc\" style=\"padding-left: 2em;\"\u003e\n                \u003ch3\u003e\u003ca href=\"/books/the-feminist-and-the-sex-offender/\" class=\"internal-link\" data-src=\"/books/the-feminist-and-the-sex-offender/\"\u003eThe Feminist and the Sex Offender\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/h3\u003e\n                \u003cp style=\"padding-bottom: 1em; padding-top: 1em;\"\u003eIn the era of #MeToo and mass incarceration, The Feminist and the Sex Offender makes a powerful feminist case for accountability without punishment and sexual safety and pleasure without injustice.\u003c/p\u003e\n            \u003c/div\u003e\n        \u003c/div\u003e\n        \u003cul class=\"tags\"\u003e\n            \n            \u003cli\u003e\u003ca href=\"/tags/non-fiction/\"\u003eNon-Fiction\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n            \n            \u003cli\u003e\u003ca href=\"/tags/book/\"\u003eBook\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n            \n            \u003cli\u003e\u003ca href=\"/tags/feminisim/\"\u003eFeminisim\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n            \n            \u003cli\u003e\u003ca href=\"/tags/politics/\"\u003ePolitics\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n            \n            \u003cli\u003e\u003ca href=\"/tags/philosophy/\"\u003ePhilosophy\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n            \n            \u003cli\u003e\u003ca href=\"/tags/theory/\"\u003eTheory\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n            \n            \u003cli\u003e\u003ca href=\"/tags/feminist-theory/\"\u003eFeminist Theory\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n            \n            \u003cli\u003e\u003ca href=\"/tags/gender/\"\u003eGender\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n            \n            \u003cli\u003e\u003ca href=\"/tags/social-justice/\"\u003eSocial Justice\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n            \n            \u003cli\u003e\u003ca href=\"/tags/academia/\"\u003eAcademia\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n            \n        \u003c/ul\u003e\n    \u003c/li\u003e\u003cli class=\"section-li\"\u003e\n        \u003cdiv class=\"section\"\u003e\n            \u003cdiv class=\"meta\"\u003e\n                \n                \u003ca href=\"/books/lost-in-work-escaping-capitalism/\"\u003e\u003cimg src=\"/imgs/lost-in-work-escaping-capitalism.png\" width=\"96px\"\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\n            \u003c/div\u003e\n            \u003cdiv class=\"desc\" style=\"padding-left: 2em;\"\u003e\n                \u003ch3\u003e\u003ca href=\"/books/lost-in-work-escaping-capitalism/\" class=\"internal-link\" data-src=\"/books/lost-in-work-escaping-capitalism/\"\u003eLost in Work Escaping Capitalism\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/h3\u003e\n                \u003cp style=\"padding-bottom: 1em; padding-top: 1em;\"\u003e\u0026lsquo;Work hard, get paid.\u0026rsquo; It\u0026rsquo;s simple. Self-evident. But it\u0026rsquo;s also a lie—at least for most of us. For young people today, the old assumptions are crumbling; hard work in school no longer guarantees a secure, well-paying job in the future.\u003c/p\u003e\n            \u003c/div\u003e\n        \u003c/div\u003e\n        \u003cul class=\"tags\"\u003e\n            \n            \u003cli\u003e\u003ca href=\"/tags/non-fiction/\"\u003eNon-Fiction\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n            \n            \u003cli\u003e\u003ca href=\"/tags/politics/\"\u003ePolitics\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n            \n            \u003cli\u003e\u003ca href=\"/tags/sociology/\"\u003eSociology\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n            \n            \u003cli\u003e\u003ca href=\"/tags/economics/\"\u003eEconomics\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n            \n            \u003cli\u003e\u003ca href=\"/tags/history/\"\u003eHistory\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n            \n            \u003cli\u003e\u003ca href=\"/tags/philosophy/\"\u003ePhilosophy\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n            \n            \u003cli\u003e\u003ca href=\"/tags/feminism/\"\u003eFeminism\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n            \n            \u003cli\u003e\u003ca href=\"/tags/labor/\"\u003eLabor\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n            \n            \u003cli\u003e\u003ca href=\"/tags/theory/\"\u003eTheory\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n            \n            \u003cli\u003e\u003ca href=\"/tags/activism/\"\u003eActivism\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n            \n            \u003cli\u003e\u003ca href=\"/tags/book/\"\u003eBook\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n            \n        \u003c/ul\u003e\n    \u003c/li\u003e\u003cli class=\"section-li\"\u003e\n        \u003cdiv class=\"section\"\u003e\n            \u003cdiv class=\"meta\"\u003e\n                \n                \u003ca href=\"/books/revolution-at-point-zero/\"\u003e\u003cimg src=\"/imgs/revolution-at-point-zero.png\" width=\"96px\"\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\n            \u003c/div\u003e\n            \u003cdiv class=\"desc\" style=\"padding-left: 2em;\"\u003e\n                \u003ch3\u003e\u003ca href=\"/books/revolution-at-point-zero/\" class=\"internal-link\" data-src=\"/books/revolution-at-point-zero/\"\u003eRevolution at Point Zero\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/h3\u003e\n                \u003cp style=\"padding-bottom: 1em; padding-top: 1em;\"\u003eWritten between 1974 and 2016, Revolution at Point Zero collects four decades of research and theorizing on the nature of housework, social reproduction, and women’s struggles on this terrain—to escape it, to better its conditions, to reconstruct it in ways that provide an alternative to capitalist relations.\u003c/p\u003e\n            \u003c/div\u003e\n        \u003c/div\u003e\n        \u003cul class=\"tags\"\u003e\n            \n            \u003cli\u003e\u003ca href=\"/tags/book/\"\u003eBook\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n            \n            \u003cli\u003e\u003ca href=\"/tags/social-science/\"\u003eSocial Science\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n            \n            \u003cli\u003e\u003ca href=\"/tags/feminism/\"\u003eFeminism\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n            \n            \u003cli\u003e\u003ca href=\"/tags/nonfiction/\"\u003eNonfiction\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n            \n            \u003cli\u003e\u003ca href=\"/tags/politics/\"\u003ePolitics\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n            \n            \u003cli\u003e\u003ca href=\"/tags/philosophy/\"\u003ePhilosophy\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n            \n            \u003cli\u003e\u003ca href=\"/tags/theory/\"\u003eTheory\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n            \n            \u003cli\u003e\u003ca href=\"/tags/essays/\"\u003eEssays\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n            \n            \u003c